Democratic Leader Nancy Pelosi expressed her support for President Obama's American Jobs Act, stating that Congress must act urgently to grow the economy and create jobs. She highlighted the plan's focus on helping small businesses, providing tax relief for workers, rebuilding infrastructure, and aiding those who have lost their jobs. Pelosi called on Republicans to work with Democrats and take immediate action to address the needs of American families. She also emphasized that Democrats have proposed a plan that aligns with the President's speech and urged House Committee Ranking Members to schedule hearings and take action on the proposed legislation.